programme.title: Wildest Islands: Japan: Islands of Extremes
programme.desc: Japan's 7,000 islands stretch for over 2,400 km, and cover an incredible range of climates. Winter in the central and northern islands can be savage, but summer in the sweltering southern islands couldn't be more different.

programme.title: Wildest Latin America: The Andes: World in the Clouds
programme.desc: The longest chain of mountains in the world, the Andes run the length of western South America and dictate the climate for the whole continent. They include some of the highest peaks outside the Himalayas.
programme.sub-title: The Andes: World in the Clouds

programme.title: Wildest Latin America: Venezuela: The Treasure of El Dorado
programme.desc: Venezuela is famous for its lost worlds, its forbidding mountains, huge swamps, and impenetrable jungles, all seemingly cut off in space and time. Yet each is linked, by the mighty river: the Orinoco, the rumoured route to El Dorado, city of gold.
programme.sub-title: Venezuela: The Treasure of El Dorado

programme.title: Wildest Latin America: Amazon: One Jungle, Many Worlds
programme.desc: The Amazon is the largest rainforest in the world, and the richest ecosystem on earth. This film uncovers what makes the Amazon such a powerhouse of evolution; how it has come to home a third of all species on the planet.

programme.title: Wildest Latin America: Patagonia: The Ends of the Earth
programme.desc: Patagonia is a place of extremes  of vast ice fields and snow-capped mountains; of windswept deserts, and violent oceans. Survival here means being tough enough to cope with brutal winters, and canny enough to exploit brief seasons of plenty.
programme.sub-title: Patagonia: The Ends of the Earth

programme.title: Wildest Latin America: Pantanal: Brazil's Wild Heart
programme.desc: Every year the Pantanal is drowned by immense floods, and then suffer severe drought. Yet, while people struggle, the Pantanal hosts some of the greatest gatherings of animals on the planet.

programme.title: Wildest India: Western Ghats: Monsoon Mountains
programme.desc: See how the Himalayas run across 2,500km of north India.The Himalayas' highlands offer little direct refuge to humans. /Then, learn about the western Ghats. A spine of mountains that lay claim to being one of the most bio-diverse places in the world.

programme.title: Wildest India: The Himalayas: Surviving the Summits
programme.desc: The Himalayas run across 2,500km of north India. he Himalayas' rugged highlands offer little direct refuge to humans, in the shadow below, over a billion people in India rely on the mountains for survival.

programme.title: Wildest India: India's Lost World
programme.desc: North-east India is an anthropological paradise; there is no other place on Earth with so many different ethnic groups. The forest are filled with mysterious tribes whose lives are dictated by the rain and the seasonal fruits of the forest.

programme.title: Wildest India: Ganges: River of Life
programme.desc: Then watch, the longest river in India, The Ganges. It's a lifeline to wild animals, from rhinoceros and river dolphins to otters and gharials.

programme.title: Wildest India: Thar Desert: Sacred Sands
programme.desc: Covering 200,000 km sq, India's Thar desert is one of the harshest places on Earth. Desiccating winds and near permanent drought has earned this unforgiving land another name: the region of death.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Madagascar: Islands of Monsters
programme.desc: Madagascar is truly a weird and wonderful land. Isolated on an island of extreme and magical looking locations, life has adapted and diversified. With few predators, numbers have proliferated and natural selection has gone mad.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Zambezi: Wild Water
programme.desc: The Zambezi is one of Africa's most influential rivers. It supports some of the continent's most spectacular wildlife. However, the Zambezi's long and winding journey destroys, as well as creates.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Mount Kenya: African Heart of Ice
programme.desc: Mount Kenya soars over 5km into the air. It is the second highest mountain in Africa. At its summit, temperatures fluctuate from over 30 degrees celsius to below freezing.
programme.sub-title: Mount Kenya: African Heart of Ice

programme.desc: Ngorongoro is thought to have formed about 2.5 million years ago from a large volcano, whose cone collapsed inward after a major eruption. This fertile land is full of wildlife, from cunning hyena and proud lions to vast herds of wildebeest and elephants.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Namibia: Sands of Time

programme.title: World's Greatest: Port Cities
programme.desc: Some of the most stunning cities are port cities - Sydney, Rio, Cape Town - and are also some of the most culturally diverse and vibrant. The great maritime cities of the world bridge countries and continents and unite the global community.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Nearshore Islands
programme.desc: Some of the world’s greatest islands are so close that they blend in with the mainland. But regardless of their size and origins, they are often the islands we are drawn to the most, each forging their own unique identity.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Remote Cities
programme.desc: Brave the frontiers of the world’s most remote cities. More than distant trading posts and isolated regional hubs, cities like Alice Springs, Jaipur and even Las Vegas serve as gateways to the wild places of the Earth.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Glaciers
programme.desc: Clinging to the world’s highest mountains and forming ice caps on both poles, glaciers leave an impression on the landscape and on all who bear witness to their splendor.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Rivers
programme.desc: Rivers flow freely - beautiful and powerful waterways that underscore the melody of life. As they meander through the landscape, they shape it, wearing down ranges and deepening valleys, eventually flowing out into the sea.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Coasts
programme.desc: Along coasts, one element ends and another begins. No two days are ever the same on a coastline: the only thing that remains a constant is the timeless power of the sea.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Grassland Animals
programme.desc: Grasslands are the great stages of the natural world where large animals play out spectacular lives in clear view of people, including lions, leopards, elephants, rhinoceros, cheetahs, impalas, kangaroos, wallaby, potoroo, bison, and wolves.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Timeless Cities & Towns
programme.desc: These cities and towns are special places where the past coexists with the present, creating cultures totally unique to their people and their part of the world and adhering to ancient traditions and while introducing modern innovations.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Deserts
programme.desc: For all their reputation as inhospitable places, deserts are full of incredible plants and animals that have adapted to the climate. They are bursting with geological wonders that inspire and are home to some of the most life in the world.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Island Nations
programme.desc: Though many are small in stature, they have punched well above their weight on the global stage. Some are rooted in ancient history, while others are only just beginning to realize their full potential.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Bridges
programme.desc: A bridge is a structure that’s designed to transcend, but a great bridge can define the place where it stands. Symbols of human ingenuity, beauty, and grandeur, bridges connect us not only to each other but also to the past.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Coral Islands
programme.desc: The reef systems that gave rise to coral islands support the vast majority of marine species on our planet, but they are under threat. Explore the delicate balance between exploiting and preserving these extraordinary natural wonders.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Flights
programme.desc: Our experience of the world’s greatest marvels is literally and figuratively elevated when we explore them from the air. Whether you travel by air balloon, helicopter, light aircraft, a grand perspective is always guaranteed.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Cruises
programme.desc: There is something seductive about setting sail. Cruises offer us a chance to dip our toes into the 70% of our planet awash with oceans, rivers, and lakes, exploring places that can only be reached by daring to leave the shore.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Iconic Buildings
programme.desc: In construction, only a few buildings can be groundbreaking. Vastly different in shape, size, and function, these diverse buildings prove there is no recipe for greatness, just the fundamental ingredients of vision, bravery, and imagination.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Land Adventures
programme.desc: Most land adventures come with some risk - a chance to confront our deepest fears, resist the pull of the ordinary, and soar into the wild unknown.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Drives
programme.desc: A journey by road expands our horizons, allowing us to explore the depth and breadth of whole countries and continents, stopping whenever and wherever we chose.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Jungle Animals
programme.desc: Encounter gorillas and orangutans, killer tree-dwelling pythons, delightful monkeys, awe-inspiring tigers, and millions of land-dwelling red crabs in Australia, the islands of Southeast Asia, Africa, and the Amazon.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Battle of Okinawa
programme.desc: Kamikaze pilots guard the island of Okinawa from American forces.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Battle of Remagen
programme.desc: German forces retreat across the Rhine on the Remagen bridge near the close of the war.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Mount Hot Rocks (February 19, 1945)
programme.desc: American forces landing on the shores of Iwo Jima encounter Japanese combatants willing to fight to the death.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Battle of the Bulge (December 1944)
programme.desc: The December 1944 battle pitting American forces against German Panzer divisions in the Ardennes Forest.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Mount Belvedere
programme.desc: The Battle of the Gothic Line in 1944.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: The Last Stronghold (November 1944)
programme.desc: American B-29 high-altitude bomber attacks Japan near the end of World War II.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory
programme.desc: Gen. Douglas MacArthur's return to the Philippines, and the final push to retake the islands after two years of Japanese occupation.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Arnhem
programme.desc: The Allies launch an attack designed to push the Germans back to the Rhine River.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Liberation of the Paris
programme.desc: Both political and military expediency were factors in the return of the French capital to its people.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Operation Dragoon (August 1944)
programme.desc: The Allies break into France and push the Germans back to their own border.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Retaking France
programme.desc: Six weeks after the D-Day invasion of the Beaches of Normandy, the allied forces are pushing the Germans back through the French countryside. Town by town is won back as Panzer divisions retreat back to the Meuse River.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: D-Day (June 6,1944)
programme.desc: D-Day, the 6th of June--one of the most pivotal moments in world history. In a massive armada of thousands of ships, 3,000,000 allied troops land at Three Beaches in Normandy, France.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Battle in Palau (Summer 1944)
programme.desc: As the United States prepared for the invasion of the Philippines, scheduled for late 1944, the tiny Palau Islands had to be taken first.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Kwajalein
programme.desc: Examining the battle at the Kwajelein Atoll in the South Pacific during 1944. Included: operations by the Seabees.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Battle of Anzio
programme.desc: Allied armies encounter German resistance in the Italian fishing town of Anzio.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: The Gilbert Islands (November 1943)
programme.desc: Bloody fighting erupts on a group of tiny Pacific islands in November 1943.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Monte Cassino (September 3, 1943)
programme.desc: As the allies make their way into Italy, they encounter tremendous resistance at German defensive positions along the Gustav line. One of these locations is an ancient monastery called Monte Cassino.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Bombing of Ploesti
programme.desc: American bombers target a Romanian oil refinery in a daring 1943 mission.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Battle of Sicily
programme.desc: Fresh from victory in North Africa, the Allies successfully invade the island of Sicily, staging an eventual Italian withdrawal from the war.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Burma: The Forgotten Front (Spring 1943)
programme.desc: The Japanese meet resistance from British forces as they advance through Burma to take India in 1944.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: North Africa (November 1942)
programme.desc: In the North African desert in 1942, American fighting forces encounter the dreaded Rommel for the first time to stop the German war machine.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: El Alamein
programme.desc: Erwin Rommel battles Allied forces in North Africa in 1942.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Battle of Stalingrad
programme.desc: German forces encounter Russian resistance.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Battle of Dieppe
programme.desc: The Allies launch an ill-fated attack on the German-occupied port of Dieppe, France.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: The Solomon Islands (July 1942)
programme.desc: For the first time since Americans entered the war, Marines face Japanese infantrymen at Guadal Canal. In the jungles, two powerful armies clash in a six month battle that claims nearly 30,000 lives.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: The Battle of Midway (June 2, 1942)
programme.desc: Only one isolated atoll prevents an enemy invasion of Hawaii. Midway Island is where the Japanese fleet converges on a tiny American base with a massive strafing and bombing attack.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Fall of the Philippines
programme.desc: Examining the Japanese invasion of the Philippines in December 1941.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Pearl Harbor (December 7, 1941)
programme.desc: During a two-hour surprise attack on the American Pacific fleet anchored at Pearl Harbor, Japanese navy pilots score a near-complete victory.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: The Fall of Singapore (October 1941)
programme.desc: Before the sneak attack on Pearl Harbor, the Japanese initiate the Pacific War by firing on the British in Malaya. Their route to the rubber-rich nation takes them into Singapore, the World's most armed fortress.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: The Battle of Malta (June 1941)
programme.desc: In 1941, Mussolini desperately wants to wrest the tiny island of Malta from the British for control of the Mediterranean. When his inadequate air force fails to bomb the Maltese into submission, Hitler's Luftwaffe joins the campaign.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Operation Mercury
programme.desc: After British forces withdrew in defeat from Greece to the island of Crete in early 1941, they were soon fighting German invasion armies again. This time, 5,000 of Hitler's elite paratroopers landed to complete their conquest in the Mediterranean.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Battle of Tobruk
programme.desc: German field marshal Erwin Rommel scores a major victory at the Libyan seaport of Tobruk.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: The Bombing of England (Fall 1940)
programme.desc: After invading France, Hitler is planning to cross the Channel. His only obstacle is the Royal Air Force. Throughout the summer of 1940, both sides lose an incredible number of daring flyers.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: The Battle of Norway (Early 1940)
programme.desc: Early in the war, the Germans decide they need to guarantee access to the Norwegian port of Narvik to ensure their supplies of Swedish iron ore. The British, however, send destroyers to up-end the German plan.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Fall of Poland
programme.desc: German tanks roll into Poland in September 1939.

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: Dunkirk (September 1, 1939)
programme.desc: To keep France free, 400,000 English soldiers have manned the battlefields. Germany's strength is too great and pushes the British to the coast town of Dunkirk.

programme.title: Rommel: The Soldier, The Son, and Hitler
programme.desc: Never a member of the Nazi party, Rommel detested blending politics and war. He would quickly discover that both were always in play under Hitler.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: X-Rated
programme.desc: Adolf Hitler had a depraved sex life that he tried to keep hidden from the German public. He was said to be a chronic masturbator, a voyeur and that he engaged in sado-masochistic sex with women.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: Body Image
programme.desc: Hitler wanted the world to believe he possessed super-human qualities but in private he was a wreck. This episode reveals the archives that confirm Hitler’s genital deformity, the alarming truth about his heavy drug addiction and the Parkinson’s.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: Family Matters
programme.desc: Adolf Hitler's father was a violent, abusive man. His mother doted on her young son. This episode delves deep into the psychology of Hitler as the narcissistic child who grew into a malignant psychopath full of rage and deep hatred.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: Suicidal Maidens
programme.desc: Using extensive archival research, this program explores the squalid secrets he lied and killed to protect

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: From The "Protection Squadron" To The SS State.
programme.desc: From the Protection Squadron to the SS State: Trace the rise to power of the SS as we examine several perpetrators. Who was recruited? And why was the SS attractive to men?
programme.sub-title: From The "Protection Squadron" To The SS State.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: Heinrich Himmler
programme.desc: Heinrich Himmler: An agriculturalist by trade, he went on to lead the SS and tried to escape responsibility at the end of the war. Who was Heinrich Himmler?

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: The Executioner: Reinhard Heydrich
programme.desc: The Executioner: Reinhard Heydrich: More than any other Nazi leader, Heydrich was an orchestrator of mass murder, and was terrifyingly clinical in approach.

programme.title: Architects Of Darkness: Adolf Hitler
programme.desc: Adolf Hitler: The film explores the roots of Adolf Hitler and traces the story of his life from the town of his birth to his final days.

programme.title: Architects Of Darkness: Heinrich Himmler
programme.desc: Heinrich Himmler: Largely due to the SS which he led, Himmler, the unsuspecting killer, was the most powerful of all of Hitler's men.

programme.title: Architects Of Darkness: Josef Goebbels
programme.desc: Josef Goebbels: A unique documentary looking at the role of Goebbels, a man from Hitler's inner circle.

programme.title: Architects Of Darkness: Julius Streicher
programme.desc: Julius Streicher: A look at the role of Julius Streicher in the Nazi regime. Streicher was responsible for much anti-Semitic propaganda

programme.title: Architects Of Darkness: Hermann Goering
programme.desc: Hermann Goering: Hermann Goering was the commander-in-chief of the Luftwaffe and Hitler's designated successor. This is his dark story.

programme.title: Architects Of Darkness: Albert Speer
programme.desc: Albert Speer: The career of Albert Speer, Hitler's architect, is explored in this documentary of dark figures.

programme.title: Einsatzgruppen: The Nazi Death Squads: Mass Graves
programme.desc: This first episode provides context for when, how and why the mobile death squads, or EZG, were established.

programme.title: Einsatzgruppen: The Nazi Death Squads: Judenfrei
programme.desc: In December 1941, after the EZG’s intervention, Romania, Bulgaria, Hungary and the Baltic states are declared 'Judenfrei': free of Jews.

programme.title: Einsatzgruppen: The Nazi Death Squads: Funeral Pyres
programme.desc: Faced with the advancing Soviet troops, Nazi Germany decided to have the bodies of the death camp victims dug up and burned in graves

programme.title: The Tender Tale Of Cinderella Penguin
programme.desc: Medieval-style animation twists Cinderella with a mistreated penguin. Hilarity ensues when she loses her magic flipper, saved by Prince Charming. A wordless film with a unique fairy tale twist.

programme.title: How They Saw Us Careers And Cradles
programme.desc: Made in 1947, this transitional film uses the celebration of token women of achievement as a way of justifying marriage as a career. It points to the emphasis on femininity and consumerism in the 1950s.

programme.title: How They Saw Us Women At Work
programme.desc: This is an abridged version of a film made in 1958. The greater part of the film accepts as normal the waste of women's talents in repetitive or service jobs, while elevating this work to the status of a career.

programme.title: The Street
programme.desc: A poignant adaptation of Mordecai Richler's short story candidly depicts families' responses to aging members. Through watercolor and ink, the filmmaker captures raw family emotions, reflecting harsh realities.

programme.title: Men of the Deeps
programme.desc: Men of the Deeps is a moving portrait of a group of former Cape Breton miners gathered together by their love of song. They are all members of the Men of the Deeps chorus, whose performances of traditional and contemporary songs evoke their working lives

programme.title: Burning Times, The
programme.desc: This film is an in-depth look at the witch-hunts that swept through Europe just a few hundred years ago. False accusations and trials led to massive torture and burnings at the stake, and ultimately to the destruction of an organic way of life.

programme.title: Canada Vignettes The Performer
programme.desc: A vignette featuring Roger Doucet singing O Canada at a hockey game in the Montréal Forum.

programme.title: The Railrodder
programme.desc: A screen short starring Buster Keaton, this is one of the last films of the comedian's long career. As "the railrodder" he crosses Canada from east to west on a railway track speeder. As might be expected, the film is full of sight gags.

programme.title: Very Nice Very Nice
programme.desc: Arthur Lipsett's debut film peels back life's facade, revealing hidden anxieties beneath. Through familiar images and fragmented speech, it critiques societal norms, punctuated by the recurring phrase, "Very nice, very nice.

programme.title: Neighbours Voisins
programme.desc: Two neighbours live side by side in harmony until a flower grows on the dividing line between their properties. Who does it belong to? The argument that follows ends up with both neighbours in their graves. The most famous of Norman McLaren’s films.

programme.title: How They Saw Us Service In The Sky
programme.desc: Made in 1957, this film glamorizes a service job in which minor emergencies appear as serious and absorbing challenges. Marriage is assumed to be the natural end of the middle-class woman's working life.

programme.title: Nails
programme.desc: A blacksmith is seen labouring at his forge, shaping nails from single strands of steel rods. It then shifts from this setting to the roar of a twentieth-century nail mill, where machines, cut, and pound the steel rods faster than the eye can follow.

programme.title: Bobs Birthday
programme.desc: Surprise birthday parties can be risky. Especially when the guest of honour is turning 40! When Margaret plans a celebration for her husband, Bob, she underestimates the sudden impact of middle age on his mood.

programme.title: Yul 871
programme.desc: A Paris engineer on Flight YUL 871 to Montréal seeks his displaced parents amid the restlessness of the era. Amidst a brief love affair and Expo visits, he finds connection with a little girl.

programme.title: Atonement
programme.desc: This film shows efforts being made by wildlife specialists to preserve and nurture the creatures that do remain in our wilderness areas. Scenes rarely photographed make this a spellbinding film throughout.

programme.title: Writer In The Nuclear Age A Conversation With Margaret Laurence
programme.desc: Margaret Laurence tackles peace-related issues in this short film: writer's social responsibility, language's impact, nuclear threat, and more. Ideal for sparking discussions across various subjects.

programme.title: The Fate Of America
programme.desc: On Sept 13, 1759, the Battle of the Plains of Abraham sealed America's fate in 20 mins. 'The Fate of America' explores this myth, leaving French Canadians pondering defeat. Filmmaker Jacques Godbout's take unites Montcalm and Wolfe's descendants.

programme.title: Illuminated Lives A Brief History Of Womens Work In The Middle Ages
programme.desc: The popular image of the Middle Ages comes from fairy tales and romances. This animated short challenges some enduring myths about medieval women and shows what their lives were really like.

programme.title: Strings
programme.desc: Strings: a haunting film of intimate strangers linked by shared spaces. Comfortable connections fracture when a problem arises. Created with glass painting and stop-motion, it's visually stunning.

programme.title: MTV Unplugged: a-ha
programme.desc: Im Juni 2017 zeichneten a-ha, das norwegische Trio mit Millionen verkaufter Platten, ein Konzert für die legendäre Reihe "MTV Unplugged" auf. Das Event fand in der Mittsommernacht auf der kleinen norwegischen Insel Giske statt.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast im Sonnenparadies Kärnten
programme.desc: Dagmar Obernosterer ist zu Gast bei Freunden. Die Original Fidelen Lavanttaler, Marc Pircher u.v.a. begeistern das Fernsehpublikum. Ob am Wörthersee, am Großglockner oder im Nationalpark Hohe Tauern - das ist Natur, die beeindruckende Geschichten erzählt.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: Berggenuss und Seenspaß
programme.desc: Kärnten hat vielleicht die schönsten Badeseen Österreichs. Viele Sonnentage und Wassertemperaturen bis 28 Grad machen Kärnten zu einem Urlaubsidyll. Musik gibt es von Andreas Gabalier, den jungen Zillertalern, Saso Avsenik und seinen Oberkrainern u.v.a.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: Winter in Kärnten
programme.desc: Dagmar Obernosterer wedelt mit den Stars der volkstümlichen Schlagermusik durch den tief verschneiten Winter in Kärnten. Deniela de Santos, Claus Marcus, Antonia, Marlena Martinelli u.v.a. erkunden die Ferienregion direkt an der italienischen Grenze.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast in Bled in Slowenien
programme.desc: Moderatorin Dagmar Obernosterer ist wieder unterwegs, um schöne Landschaften und viel Musik zu präsentieren. Dieses Mal verschlägt es sie nach Bled in Slowenien. Begleitet wird sie von Volksmusikstars wie den Zellberg Buam, Belsy und Udo Wenders.
programme.sub-title: zu Gast in Bled in Slowenien

programme.title: Hitcocktail
programme.desc: Du bist das Leben / Von hier bis unendlich / Deine Liebe / Jenseits der Zeit / Einfach mal gar nichts tun / Meilenweit / Frieden fängt im Herzen an / Diamanten / Gestern war's noch Liebe / Frau aller Frauen

programme.title: Die Flippers
programme.desc: Die Flippers reisen an die Côte d´Azur. Ihr Weg führt sie nach St. Tropez, nach Nizza und zu den Reichen und Schönen nach Monaco. Begleitet wird die musikalische Reise vom französischen Charme der Tänzer- und Sängerin Marlène Charell.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast in Antholz
programme.desc: Dagmar Obernosterer begibt sich auf kulinarische Reise durch das schöne Antholzertal und macht Erfahrungen beim Biathlon. Sie blickt auf vergangene Sendungen zurück und begrüßt die Schäfer, Simone, die Alpenoberkrainer, Rudy Giovannini, u.v.a.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: im Lungau
programme.desc: Dagmar Obernosterer präsentiert den Lungauer Almsommer aus dem Salzburgerland. Stars wie das Nockalm Quintett, Marc Pircher, die Meissnitzer Band, die Edlseer, die Oberkrainer aus Begunje u.v.a. machen die Sendung zu einem unvergesslichen Fernseherlebnis.

programme.title: Schlagergala 2006: Teil 2
programme.desc: Auch im 2. Teil der A.D.S.-Schlagergala zeigt GoldStar TV die Höhepunkte der Show. Beim Konzert beweisen Stars wie Kristina Bach, Nino de Angelo, Jürgen Drews und viele mehr, dass sie zu den Größten des deutschen Schlagers gehören.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast in Tirols Sport & Vital Park am Achensee
programme.desc: Diesmal lädt Dagmar Obernosterer an den Achensee ein. Zwischen dem Karwendel und dem Rofangebirge liegt der größte See Tirols, der an einen norwegischen Fjord erinnert. Natürlich gibt es auch wieder viel Musik u.a. von Monika Martin und den Zillertalern.
programme.sub-title: zu Gast in Tirols Sport & Vital Park am Achensee

programme.title: Olaf Henning - Volles Programm: Teil 2
programme.desc: Wo er auftaucht ist Stimmung. Seine Hits sorgen in Deutschland und auf Mallorca für beste Partystimmung. Das Konzert "Volles Programm" zeigt Olaf Henning live mit seinen größten Hits.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast im frühlingshaften Südtirol
programme.desc: Nicht nur Musikliebhaber und Blumenfreunde werden begeistert sein, wenn Dagmar Obernosterer die Stars der Volksmusik präsentiert. Rund um das Blütenparadies von Schloss Trauttmansdorff erklingen Hits von Oswald Sattler, den Kastelruther Spatzen u.v.a.

programme.title: Die Flippers
programme.desc: Die Flippers im Land des "Dolce Vita". Sie besuchen die schönsten Orte Italiens, u.a. Venedig, die wohl romantischste Stadt der Welt. Vor weltberühmter Kulisse präsentieren sie Evergreens wie "Oh Sole Mio", "Santa Lucia" oder "Capri Fischer".

programme.title: So schön ist der Norden: Mecklenburg Vorpommern
programme.desc: Mecklenburg-Vorpommern ist eine Reise wert. Alles dreht sich um das Bundesland mit den meisten Nationalparks in Deutschland und um seine herrlichen Schlösser und Herrenhäuser. Musikalische Gäste sind u.a Patrick Lindner, WIND und Susan Ebrahimi.

programme.title: So schön ist der Norden: Heiligendamm
programme.desc: Frederic Meisner und Sarah Winkhaus lassen sich den Ostseewind um die Nase wehen und besuchen den Ort, an dem der Strandkorb erfunden wurde. Auch musikalisch weht ein frischer Wind. Stars wie Mary Roos, Olaf Berger u.v.a. präsentieren ihre großen Hits.

programme.title: Tanzparty
programme.desc: Ein Bett im Kornfeld / One For You, One For Me / Love Is In The Air / Ma baker / Na Na Hey Hey Goodbye / How Do You Do / Dolce vita / Maria Magdalena / Das gewisse Gefühl

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast in der Wachau und Bruck an der Mur
programme.desc: Viele Stars der Volksmusik begleiten Dagmar Obernosterer durch die malerische Hügellandschaft der Wachau. Petra Frey, Oswald Sattler, Simone u.v.a. verwöhnen Sie auf der Reise von Dürnstein über Bruck a. d. Mur bis nach Gamlitz mit ihren Liedern.
programme.sub-title: zu Gast in der Wachau und Bruck an der Mur

programme.title: Ein Festival der Liebe: Teil 1
programme.desc: Es war das Open Air des Jahres. Im Revierpark Wischlingen in Dortmund feierte GoldStar TV mit tausenden Schlagerfans sein 10-jähriges Bestehen. Beim "Festival der Liebe" gaben sich Stars wie Ireen Sheer, Wind und Kristina Bach ein Stelldichein.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast in St. Veit an der Glan (Kärnten)
programme.desc: Heimatlich und mit einem Hauch von Mystik, so präsentiert sich diese Ausgabe von "Lieder, Land & Leute" . Mit dabei, wenn es in die wunderschöne Landschaft rund um St. Veit a. d. Glan geht, sind Petra Frey, die Zellberg Buam, das Alpentrio Tirol, u.v.a.
programme.sub-title: zu Gast in St. Veit an der Glan (Kärnten)

programme.title: The Christmas Star
programme.desc: Incluso las estrellas se enfrentan a los mismos problemas que los humanos. Un día, la celosa Próxima derriba a Morning Star del cielo y ésta aterriza en un pueblo. Morning Star sólo tiene unos días para volver al cielo, de lo contrario se extinguirá.

programme.title: Homemade Christmas
programme.desc: Cada año, una joven quiere convertirse en la mejor asistente para contratar en Navidad. Pero cuando llega la oportunidad de salvar una fiesta de Navidad y deslumbrar a la persona que le gusta, deberá elegir entre sus aspiraciones y el hombre perfecto.

programme.title: Christmas Wedding Runaway
programme.desc: Una novia fugitiva hace una búsqueda espiritual cuando es atrapada por la nieve dentro de una cabaña con su abuela y un viejo amor en Navidad.

programme.title: Las navidades de Pete
programme.desc: Petes Christmas es una película para televisión protagonizada por Zachary Gordon y Bailee Madison. Un niño se encuentra en el centro de atención inesperado cuando se da cuenta de que el terrible día de Navidad de su familia sigue repitiéndose.

programme.title: Mejor Solo Que Mal Acompañado
programme.desc: Neal quería volar a Chicago para pasar el Día de Acción de Gracias con su familia. Pero solo consigue problemas. Problemas causados por Del Griffith, un vendedor gritón que lleva a Neal en un viaje salvaje.

programme.title: 12 Regalos de navidad
programme.desc: Cuando Anna, una pintora desempleada, no puede llegar a fin de mes, la contratan para convertirse en la compradora navideña personal de Marc, un ejecutivo corporativo tenso.

programme.title: Deliciosa Navidad
programme.desc: Máximo, chef de cocina molecular, hereda un restaurante dirigido por Luciana, experta en cocina típica. Durante la Navidad, ambos se enfrentan por sus diferentes visiones de la vida, la cocina y el amor, creando una combinación explosiva y deliciosa.

programme.title: Spotlight on Christmas
programme.desc: Abandonada dos semanas antes de Navidad, la actriz de Hollywood Olivia O'Hara regresa en secreto a su pequeña ciudad natal para evitar a la prensa. Cuando se topa con el profesor de secundaria Casey, él la anima a dirigir la obra navideña de su escuela.

programme.title: Fabric of Christmas, The
programme.desc: Liam, un bombero, y Amy, una profesora de acolchado, se unen para hacer una colcha navideña para la boda de la hermana de Liam, pero su romance se ve amenazado por el plan de Liam de viajar a Sudamérica.

programme.title: Una Navidad Casi Perfecta
programme.desc: Tras perder su trabajo y novio, una aspirante a novelista se muda a Sunshine Coast y descubre las complejidades del amor.

programme.title: The Christmas Star
programme.desc: Incluso las estrellas se enfrentan a los mismos problemas que los humanos. Un día, la celosa Próxima derriba a Morning Star del cielo y ésta aterriza en un pueblo. Morning Star sólo tiene unos días para volver al cielo, de lo contrario se extinguirá.

programme.title: Homemade Christmas
programme.desc: Cada año, una joven quiere convertirse en la mejor asistente para contratar en Navidad. Pero cuando llega la oportunidad de salvar una fiesta de Navidad y deslumbrar a la persona que le gusta, deberá elegir entre sus aspiraciones y el hombre perfecto.

programme.title: Christmas Wedding Runaway
programme.desc: Una novia fugitiva hace una búsqueda espiritual cuando es atrapada por la nieve dentro de una cabaña con su abuela y un viejo amor en Navidad.

programme.title: Las navidades de Pete
programme.desc: Petes Christmas es una película para televisión protagonizada por Zachary Gordon y Bailee Madison. Un niño se encuentra en el centro de atención inesperado cuando se da cuenta de que el terrible día de Navidad de su familia sigue repitiéndose.

programme.title: Mejor Solo Que Mal Acompañado
programme.desc: Neal quería volar a Chicago para pasar el Día de Acción de Gracias con su familia. Pero solo consigue problemas. Problemas causados por Del Griffith, un vendedor gritón que lleva a Neal en un viaje salvaje.

programme.title: 12 Regalos de navidad
programme.desc: Cuando Anna, una pintora desempleada, no puede llegar a fin de mes, la contratan para convertirse en la compradora navideña personal de Marc, un ejecutivo corporativo tenso.

programme.title: Deliciosa Navidad
programme.desc: Máximo, chef de cocina molecular, hereda un restaurante dirigido por Luciana, experta en cocina típica. Durante la Navidad, ambos se enfrentan por sus diferentes visiones de la vida, la cocina y el amor, creando una combinación explosiva y deliciosa.

programme.title: Spotlight on Christmas
programme.desc: Abandonada dos semanas antes de Navidad, la actriz de Hollywood Olivia O'Hara regresa en secreto a su pequeña ciudad natal para evitar a la prensa. Cuando se topa con el profesor de secundaria Casey, él la anima a dirigir la obra navideña de su escuela.

programme.title: Fabric of Christmas, The
programme.desc: Liam, un bombero, y Amy, una profesora de acolchado, se unen para hacer una colcha navideña para la boda de la hermana de Liam, pero su romance se ve amenazado por el plan de Liam de viajar a Sudamérica.

programme.title: Una Navidad Casi Perfecta
programme.desc: Tras perder su trabajo y novio, una aspirante a novelista se muda a Sunshine Coast y descubre las complejidades del amor.

programme.sub-title: Mariah Carey / Andy Williams / George Ezra / Sam Smith / Wham! / Summer Walker & Love Renaissance / David Bowie & Bing Crosby

programme.title: The Christmas Star
programme.desc: Incluso las estrellas se enfrentan a los mismos problemas que los humanos. Un día, la celosa Próxima derriba a Morning Star del cielo y ésta aterriza en un pueblo. Morning Star sólo tiene unos días para volver al cielo, de lo contrario se extinguirá.

programme.title: Homemade Christmas
programme.desc: Cada año, una joven quiere convertirse en la mejor asistente para contratar en Navidad. Pero cuando llega la oportunidad de salvar una fiesta de Navidad y deslumbrar a la persona que le gusta, deberá elegir entre sus aspiraciones y el hombre perfecto.

programme.title: Christmas Wedding Runaway
programme.desc: Una novia fugitiva hace una búsqueda espiritual cuando es atrapada por la nieve dentro de una cabaña con su abuela y un viejo amor en Navidad.

programme.title: Las navidades de Pete
programme.desc: Petes Christmas es una película para televisión protagonizada por Zachary Gordon y Bailee Madison. Un niño se encuentra en el centro de atención inesperado cuando se da cuenta de que el terrible día de Navidad de su familia sigue repitiéndose.

programme.title: Mejor Solo Que Mal Acompañado
programme.desc: Neal quería volar a Chicago para pasar el Día de Acción de Gracias con su familia. Pero solo consigue problemas. Problemas causados por Del Griffith, un vendedor gritón que lleva a Neal en un viaje salvaje.

programme.title: 12 Regalos de navidad
programme.desc: Cuando Anna, una pintora desempleada, no puede llegar a fin de mes, la contratan para convertirse en la compradora navideña personal de Marc, un ejecutivo corporativo tenso.

programme.title: Deliciosa Navidad
programme.desc: Máximo, chef de cocina molecular, hereda un restaurante dirigido por Luciana, experta en cocina típica. Durante la Navidad, ambos se enfrentan por sus diferentes visiones de la vida, la cocina y el amor, creando una combinación explosiva y deliciosa.

programme.title: Spotlight on Christmas
programme.desc: Abandonada dos semanas antes de Navidad, la actriz de Hollywood Olivia O'Hara regresa en secreto a su pequeña ciudad natal para evitar a la prensa. Cuando se topa con el profesor de secundaria Casey, él la anima a dirigir la obra navideña de su escuela.

programme.title: Fabric of Christmas, The
programme.desc: Liam, un bombero, y Amy, una profesora de acolchado, se unen para hacer una colcha navideña para la boda de la hermana de Liam, pero su romance se ve amenazado por el plan de Liam de viajar a Sudamérica.

programme.title: Una Navidad Casi Perfecta
programme.desc: Tras perder su trabajo y novio, una aspirante a novelista se muda a Sunshine Coast y descubre las complejidades del amor.

programme.desc: Die Stille der Natur ist nur Fassade. Das Leben ist bestimmt von Anstrengungen und Kämpfen, großen und kleinen, die zu Sieg oder Niederlage führen. Diese Kämpfe betreffen alle und alles: Kämpfe um Essen, um Reviere und um Liebe.

programme.title: Wilde Überlebenskünstler

In dieser Serie geht es um sie alle. Geschichten voller Leidenschaft, Gewalt und Zärtlichkeit bringen uns unsere tierischen Nachbarn näher von Quallen bis Elefanten, von Ameisen bis Löwen.

programme.title: Waschbären, unsere neuen Nachbarn?
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Ursprünglich stammen Waschbären aus Nordamerika. Inzwischen breiten sie sich auch in Europa aus. Da sie 2016 von der EU als invasiv, also als Gefahr für das Ökosystem eingestuft wurden, werden sie massiv bejagt. Die Berliner Tierärztin Dr. Mathilde Laininger engagiert sich für ein friedliches Miteinander zwischen Mensch und Waschbär.

programme.title: Leben mit dem Tod
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Auf der indonesischen Insel Sulawesi dreht sich schon zu Lebzeiten der Bewohner alles die Beerdigung. Der Totenkult der Toraja kann viel Geld verschlingen, was die Bestattung verstorbener Verwandter oft auf Jahre unmöglich macht. So behalten die Angehörigen ihre Toten so lange im Haus, bis sie das Geld für die aufwendigen Feierlichkeiten haben.

programme.title: Just Cooking | Trailer
programme.desc: Just Cooking bringt Kochbegeisterten das einzigartige Paket an frischen neuen Food-Trends und junger Kreativität auf den TV. Aber auch Klassiker und traditionelle Küche, sowie kulinarische Dokumentationen und Reisevlogs werden gezeigt.

programme.title: Handgemacht in Laos
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: In Asien wird Rattan vielseitig verwendet: zur Herstellung von Möbeln, Korbwaren, Wandverkleidungen und Sportbällen. Auch im bergreichen Zentrum von Laos gedeiht die stachelige Rattan-Palme. Wild als Kletter-Liane in den Dschungelwäldern, sowie angebaut auf Feldern. Die Menschen in den Dörfern ringsum leben seit Generationen von Rattan.

programme.title: Peloponnes
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Im Süden Griechenlands am Peloponnes ist der Alltag, hauptsächlich von der Landwirtschaft geprägt. Mit der Rückkehr der jungen Generation auf das Land ihrer Familien keimt Hoffnung: Permakultur und Agroforstwirtschaft sollen das in der Vergangenheit durch Monokulturen und Brände ausgelaugte Land zu neuem Leben erwecken.

programme.title: Freiheit auf Pferderücken
programme.sub-title: Der lange Weg der Nez Perce
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: 1877 weigerten sich rund 750 Angehörige des Stammes der Nez Perce, im Nordwesten der USA, ihre Freiheit aufzugeben und sich in ein Reservat zu begeben. Stattdessen begaben sie sich mit 2.000 Pferden, überwiegend Appaloosas, auf eine abenteuerliche und verlustreiche Flucht über gut 2.000 km quer durch die Rocky Mountains.

programme.title: Champagner für alle!
programme.desc: Spätsommer, Erntezeit. Die Sonne wärmt mit ihren letzten Strahlen die Spätburgunder-, Schwarzriesling- und Chardonnay-Trauben der Champagne. Hier entsteht der einzigartige französische Schaumwein, gekeltert ausschließlich nach den strengen Regeln der heimischen Winzer: Champagner! Planet Weltweit hat zwei namhafte Champagner-Winzer besucht und spürt der Philosophie der perlenden Lebensfreude nach.

programme.title: Das Land, in dem die Aprikosen blühen
programme.desc: Millionen goldgelber Früchte trocknen in der Sonne. Sie werden auch das Gold aus dem Zweistromland? genannt, die saftigen Aprikosen aus Anatolien. Auf den Plantagen an den Ufern des Euphrat wachsen 95 Prozent aller weltweit verarbeiteten Aprikosen. Doch die Idylle trügt: Hinter der malerischen Fassade brodeln Konflikte mit den alten Patriarchen um mehr Selbstbestimmung, und über allem schwebt die Sorge um die Klimaschwankungen und deren Auswirkungen auf die Ernte. Diese Dokumentation hat nicht nur die Aprikosenernte festgehalten, sondern wurde Zeuge einer Familie im Umbruch.

programme.title: Armeniens Früchte aus dem Paradies
programme.desc: Granatäpfel gehören zu den ältesten Kulturfrüchten der Menschheit. Wissenschaftler glauben sogar, dass der Baum der Erkenntnis? im Alten Testament ein Granatapfelbaum war. In Armenien ist die paradiesische Frucht Nationalsymbol. Das Land gilt als eines der Hauptanbaugebiete weltweit. Die besten Früchte werden im Süden, rund um das Dorf Nrnadzor, geerntet. Mukutsch Bojadyan ist einer der erfolgreichsten Granatapfelbauern des Dorfes. Im Oktober erntet er seine Früchte, nachdem er das ganze Jahr über Wetterkapriolen, Wasserknappheit und Bären getrotzt hat. Planet Weltweit hat ihn und seine Paradiesfrüchte besucht.

programme.title: China Moses, Joe Armon Jones & Luke Wynter
programme.sub-title: China Moses: 'Whatever' at Jazz à Ramatuelle
programme.desc: In 1988, Dee Dee Bridgewater was one of the first great jazz singers to perform at the Jazz Festival in Ramatuelle. In 2016, the story seems to repeat itself as her daughter China Moses took the stage at Ramatuelle. Over the years, China Moses has become a mature performer with a unique style: rocky voice, sharp sense of swing, and intense/energetic stage presence. After signing compilations dedicated to Dinah Washington and blues, Moses released in 2016 an album of his own compositions, entitled "Whatever". Get ready for a most entertaining performance combining jazz, soul, and hip-hop.

programme.title: Yumi Ito
programme.desc: An extraordinary collection of clips in all jazz genres from the most beautiful concerts and the most special festivals, performed by the finest jazz musicians.

programme.title: Charles Mingus, Jaki Byard, Dannie Richmond & Johnny Coles
programme.sub-title: Charles Mingus And Eric Dolphy live in Liège
programme.desc: Charles Mingus showcases an exceptional concert performed in April 1965 featuring his most celebrated lineup: Jaki Byard (piano), Dannie Richmond (drums), Johnny Coles (trumpet), Clifford Jordan (tenor sax) and the great Eric Dolphy (alto sax, flute and bass clarinet). Recorded within an eight-day span, less than three months before Dolphy's death, the three concerts showcase Mingus's visionary leadership and the band's incredible depth and diversity with unique performances and arrangements of classics including ‘So Long Eric' and the groundbreaking ‘Meditations On Integration'.

programme.title: Miles Davis
programme.desc: American trumpeter Miles Davis (1926-1991) was a pioneering jazz musician from the late 1940s to the late 1980s. His influence on 20th century music is hard to overstate, as he trailblazed bebop, cool jazz, hardbop, modal jazz, and electronic music. On October 11, 1964, Miles Davis performed at Teatro Dell'Arte in Milan. With tenor saxophonist Wayne Shorter, pianist Herbie Hancock, bassist Ron Carter and drummer Tony Williams, Davis performed Autumn Leaves, My Funny Valentine, All Blues, All of You, and Joshua.

programme.title: Stochelo Rosenberg & Peter Beets
programme.desc: The treasured compositions of guitarist Django Reinhardt, the founding father of hot club jazz, are engraved in everyone's memory. Although Reinhardt missed two fingers of his left hand, his virtuoso technique was unrivalled. Dutch guitarist Stochelo Rosenberg and pianist Peter Beets now have the pleasure to bring Django's music back to life with their infectious improvisations.

programme.title: Wes Montgomery
programme.sub-title: Herbie Man & Sonny Sharrock - Memphis underground
programme.desc: This selection of unforgettable performances by some of the most iconic and influential jazz guitarists in history showcases these legends' unique essence. Revel in Wes Montgomery's virtuosity as he performs the captivating “Nica's Dream” in Holland in 1965, and delight in the expressive beauty of his rendition of “Here's That Rainy Day”, recorded in London in that same year. Experience the timeless appeal of Joe Pass's “You Stepped Out of a Dream” and “You Turned The Tables on Me”, recorded live in Hanover in 1975. The interplay between Jim Hall and Atilla Zoller borders on the impossible as they perform “Extensions” in Hanover in 1973. Enjoy Jim Hall's lyrical solo performance of “I'm Getting Sentimental Over You” from 1964. Witness Sonny Sharrock's avant-garde fusion of jazz and rock in an exhilarating performance of “Peanut", recorded live in France in 1970. Sharrock is joined by flutist Herbie Mann in a soulful performance of “Memphis Underground” from 1969. Immerse yourself in the magic of jazz guitar!

programme.title: Omar Sosa, Childo Tomas, Ernesto Simpson & Leandro Saint-Hill
programme.desc: While always keeping one foot firmly anchored in the traditions of his home country, Cuba, Omar Sosa tirelessly explores music from the Caribbean to India, and West Africa to the Arab world. Since he left Cuba in 1993, the pianist has been blending his Afro-Cuban roots with jazz, hip hop, electro and world music. For his 2018 performance at Théâtre de Villefranche-sur-Saône, he brings to stage his Quarteto Afrocubano members Childo Tomas (electric bass & vocals), Ernesto Simpson (drums), and Leandro Saint-Hill (saxophones, flute, percussion & vocals). Together, they create a riveting instrumental dialogue. Celebrating rhythm in all its forms, this Omar Sosa concert is an intense and mystical experience.

programme.title: B.B.King
programme.sub-title: B.B. King Orchestra - The North Sea Jazz
programme.desc: The North Sea Jazz Festival is the largest indoor music festival in the world, known globally as the event where the past, present and future of jazz are featured within three days. Next to a firm base of jazz as the festival's staple music genre, many others, such as blues, soul, funk, or hip hop, pass by. Back in 1979, legendary American blues guitarist B.B. King gave an unforgettable performance for the audience in The Hague. Born in 1925 in a small town in Mississippi, 'Lucille' (as he nicknamed his guitar) helped him escape a miserable existence picking cotton. He arrived in Memphis in the late 1940s, where his cousin Bukka White taught him the tricks of the blues. Soon he developed his own style. King's virtuoso, narrative solos with lots of vibrato, have been an inspiration for most (rock) guitarists after him.

programme.title: Diana Ross & The Supremes
programme.desc: Diana Ross & Supremes- America's most successful female vocal group of all time was formed by four Detroit schoolgirls in the late 50s. Diana Ross (26 March 1944, Detroit, Michigan, USA), Betty McGlown (b. 1943, Detroit, Michigan, USA), Florence Ballard (b. 30 June 1943, Rosetta, Mississippi, USA, d. 22 February 1976, Detroit, Michigan, USA) and Mary Wilson (b. 6 March 1944, Greenville, Mississippi, USA) named themselves the Primettes in tribute to the local male group, the Primes - who themselves found fame in the 60s as the Temptations.

programme.title: Lenny Kravitz
programme.desc: American singer, songwriter, multi-instrumentalist, record producer, actor and arranger, whose "retro" style incorporates elements of rock, blues, soul, R&B, funk, jazz, reggae, hard rock, psychedelic, pop, folk and ballads. In addition to singing lead and backing vocals, Kravitz often plays all the guitar, bass, drums, keyboards, and percussion himself when recording. He won the Grammy Award for Best Male Rock Vocal Performance four years in a row from 1999 to 2002, breaking the record for most wins in that category as well as setting the record for most consecutive wins in one category by a male.

programme.title: David Grimal & Les Dissonances
programme.sub-title: Beethoven - Symphony No. 4 in B-flat major, Op. 60
programme.desc: Les Dissonances is a collective of artists founded by violinist David Grimal in 2004. The conductorless ensemble consists of musicians from the most prestigious European orchestras, international soloists, and young talents. In this performance, Les Dissonances perform Ludwig van Beethoven's Symphony No. 4 in B-flat major, Op. 60. Count Franz von Oppersdorff, who adored Beethoven's Symphony No. 2, offered the composer a large sum to write a similar work. Completed in the autumn of 1806, the symphony's first performance was at a private concert in Vienna in March of 1807. Symphony No. 4 is often overshadowed by its revolutionary predecessor and successor. With its lightweight and cheerful nature, Symphony No. 4 contrasts with the two aforementioned works. This performance was recorded at Opéra de Dijon, France, in 2013.

programme.title: David Grimal & Les Dissonances
programme.desc: Les Dissonances is a collective of artists founded by violinist David Grimal in 2004. The conductorless ensemble consists of musicians from the most prestigious European orchestras, international soloists, and young talents. In this performance, Les Dissonances perform Johannes Brahms' String Sextet No. 1 in B-flat major, Op. 18. The work is scored for two violins, two violas, and two cellos. Brahms wrote his only two string sextets at the very beginning of his career. String Sextet No. 1 was written in 1860. Brahms was one of the first to compose for this ensemble, blazing a trail for Antonín Dvořák, Pyotr Ilyich Tchaikovsky, Arnold Schoenberg, and others. This performance was recorded at Opéra de Dijon, France, in 2013.

programme.title: Claudio Abbado, Simón Bolívar Youth Orchestra & Anna Prohaska
programme.desc: Claudio Abbado conducts the Símon Bolívar Youth Orchestra at the Lucerne Easter Festival of 2010. Soloist is the young and talented Austrian soprano Anna Prohaska. On the program are Sergei Prokofiev's “Scythian Suite”, Op. 20, Alban Berg's Lulu Suite for soprano and orchestra, and Pamina's Aria from W. A. Mozart's opera The Magic Flute. The orchestra concludes with a performance of Pyotr Ilyich Tchaikovsky's Symphony No. 6, Op. 74.

programme.title: Gabriela Montero, Youth Orchestra of the Americas & Carlos Miguel Prieto
programme.desc: Venezuelan pianist Gabriela Montero is accompanied by the Youth Orchestra of the Americas conducted by Carlos Miguel Prieto. On the program are Maurice Ravel's Piano Concerto in G Major, as well as two of Montero's own works: the “Latin Concerto” and Improvisations. The performance took place in one of the world's most beautiful concert halls, the Teatro del Lago in Frutillar, located in the middle of the Patagonian plains. The concert hall, which opened its doors in 2010, stands on the banks of Chile's second-largest lake overlooking a volcano that is capped with snow the entire year. In an accompanying interview, Montero speaks about composing, improvising, and performing works of her own alongside those of others. She discusses her home country of Venezuela, where she no longer performs for political reasons.

programme.title: Kinderstube Wildnis Bei den Löwen
programme.desc: Eine alleinerziehende Löwin hat es nicht leicht in Afrikas Savannen. Löwen-Mama Nyota hat keine Beschützer und muss für sich und ihren fünf Monate alten Sohn Moja ganz alleine sorgen. Vor der Regenzeit sind Beutetiere spärlich und die besten Reviere von großen Löwenrudeln besetzt. Auf sich alleine gestellt, muss Nyota zwischen ihrem knurrenden Magen und dem Schutz des Kleinen abwägen. Es gelingt ihr kaum, sich einmal satt zu essen. Entweder die Jagdversuche bleiben erfolglos oder Hyänen machen ihr das mühsam erlegte Wild nach wenigen Bissen streitig. Alleine hat sie den Aasfressern kaum etwas entgegen zu setzen. Um Moja nicht in Gefahr zu bringen, verzichtet sie jedoch auf einen Kampf und überlässt ihren Fang der gierigen Meute. Berührende Szenen zeigen, wie das Duo trotz der immer weiter schwindenden Kräfte auch in den härtesten Wochen zusammenhält. Die Rettung der kleinen Familie naht in Form der heraufziehenden Gnu-Herden.

programme.title: Waschbären, unsere neuen Nachbarn?
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Ursprünglich stammen Waschbären aus Nordamerika. Inzwischen breiten sie sich auch in Europa aus. Da sie 2016 von der EU als invasiv, also als Gefahr für das Ökosystem eingestuft wurden, werden sie massiv bejagt. Die Berliner Tierärztin Dr. Mathilde Laininger engagiert sich für ein friedliches Miteinander zwischen Mensch und Waschbär.

programme.title: Leben mit dem Tod
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Auf der indonesischen Insel Sulawesi dreht sich schon zu Lebzeiten der Bewohner alles die Beerdigung. Der Totenkult der Toraja kann viel Geld verschlingen, was die Bestattung verstorbener Verwandter oft auf Jahre unmöglich macht. So behalten die Angehörigen ihre Toten so lange im Haus, bis sie das Geld für die aufwendigen Feierlichkeiten haben.

programme.title: Just Cooking | Trailer
programme.desc: Just Cooking bringt Kochbegeisterten das einzigartige Paket an frischen neuen Food-Trends und junger Kreativität auf den TV. Aber auch Klassiker und traditionelle Küche, sowie kulinarische Dokumentationen und Reisevlogs werden gezeigt.

programme.title: Handgemacht in Laos
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: In Asien wird Rattan vielseitig verwendet: zur Herstellung von Möbeln, Korbwaren, Wandverkleidungen und Sportbällen. Auch im bergreichen Zentrum von Laos gedeiht die stachelige Rattan-Palme. Wild als Kletter-Liane in den Dschungelwäldern, sowie angebaut auf Feldern. Die Menschen in den Dörfern ringsum leben seit Generationen von Rattan.

programme.title: Peloponnes
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Im Süden Griechenlands am Peloponnes ist der Alltag, hauptsächlich von der Landwirtschaft geprägt. Mit der Rückkehr der jungen Generation auf das Land ihrer Familien keimt Hoffnung: Permakultur und Agroforstwirtschaft sollen das in der Vergangenheit durch Monokulturen und Brände ausgelaugte Land zu neuem Leben erwecken.

programme.title: Freiheit auf Pferderücken
programme.sub-title: Der lange Weg der Nez Perce
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: 1877 weigerten sich rund 750 Angehörige des Stammes der Nez Perce, im Nordwesten der USA, ihre Freiheit aufzugeben und sich in ein Reservat zu begeben. Stattdessen begaben sie sich mit 2.000 Pferden, überwiegend Appaloosas, auf eine abenteuerliche und verlustreiche Flucht über gut 2.000 km quer durch die Rocky Mountains.

programme.title: Champagner für alle!
programme.desc: Spätsommer, Erntezeit. Die Sonne wärmt mit ihren letzten Strahlen die Spätburgunder-, Schwarzriesling- und Chardonnay-Trauben der Champagne. Hier entsteht der einzigartige französische Schaumwein, gekeltert ausschließlich nach den strengen Regeln der heimischen Winzer: Champagner! Planet Weltweit hat zwei namhafte Champagner-Winzer besucht und spürt der Philosophie der perlenden Lebensfreude nach.

programme.title: Das Land, in dem die Aprikosen blühen
programme.desc: Millionen goldgelber Früchte trocknen in der Sonne. Sie werden auch das Gold aus dem Zweistromland? genannt, die saftigen Aprikosen aus Anatolien. Auf den Plantagen an den Ufern des Euphrat wachsen 95 Prozent aller weltweit verarbeiteten Aprikosen. Doch die Idylle trügt: Hinter der malerischen Fassade brodeln Konflikte mit den alten Patriarchen um mehr Selbstbestimmung, und über allem schwebt die Sorge um die Klimaschwankungen und deren Auswirkungen auf die Ernte. Diese Dokumentation hat nicht nur die Aprikosenernte festgehalten, sondern wurde Zeuge einer Familie im Umbruch.

programme.title: Armeniens Früchte aus dem Paradies
programme.desc: Granatäpfel gehören zu den ältesten Kulturfrüchten der Menschheit. Wissenschaftler glauben sogar, dass der Baum der Erkenntnis? im Alten Testament ein Granatapfelbaum war. In Armenien ist die paradiesische Frucht Nationalsymbol. Das Land gilt als eines der Hauptanbaugebiete weltweit. Die besten Früchte werden im Süden, rund um das Dorf Nrnadzor, geerntet. Mukutsch Bojadyan ist einer der erfolgreichsten Granatapfelbauern des Dorfes. Im Oktober erntet er seine Früchte, nachdem er das ganze Jahr über Wetterkapriolen, Wasserknappheit und Bären getrotzt hat. Planet Weltweit hat ihn und seine Paradiesfrüchte besucht.

programme.title: [신비롭고 아름다운 비경] 청송 주산지 EP.5
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널주산지는 조선 경종(1720년) 10월에 준공하였습니다. 주산지의 맑은 물은 주산현 꼭대기 별바위에서 계곡을 따라 흘러 주산지에 머무르고 주왕산 영봉에서 뻗친 울창한 수림으로 둘러싸여 있으며, 물위에 떠있는 듯한 왕버들과 어우러져 별천지에 온 것 같이 한적하면서도 아늑한 분위기를 자아냅니다. ※ 청송 주산지 일원 (명승 제 105호) / 청송세계지질공원 (2017년 유네스코 세계지질공원)

programme.title: [창덕궁 봄꽃 개화 현장] 봄꽃의 향연, 창덕궁 나들이
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널창덕궁은 태종 때 건립된 조선왕조의 왕궁으로, 처음에는 경복궁의 이궁으로 지어졌지만 경복궁보다 더욱 오래 법궁의 역할을 해왔습니다. 특히 창덕궁 후원은 한국의 유일한 궁궐후원이라는 점에서 그 가치가 매우 높지요. 한국의 대표적인 정원인 창덕궁이 봄을 맞이하는 아름다운 모습을 감상해보세요! ※ 창덕궁 (사적 제122호, 1997년 유네스코 세계문화유산)

programme.title: [궁궐 속 비밀의 화원] 창덕궁 낙선재 후원 EP.1
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널낙선재는 헌종 대에 지어진 건물로, 사대부 주택의 형식을 따랐으나 궁궐 침전의 양식이 가미되었습니다. 때문에 다른 곳에서는 쉽게 찾아볼 수 없는 다양한 문양의 장식이 있어 조선 후기 건축의 축적된 기량을 엿볼 수 있죠. 일반인 비공개 지역인 창덕궁 낙선재 후원을 바라보며 휴식을 취해보세요. ※ 창덕궁 낙선재 (보물 1764호) / 창덕궁 (1997년 유네스코 세계문화유산)

programme.title: China Moses, Joe Armon Jones & Luke Wynter
programme.sub-title: China Moses: 'Whatever' at Jazz à Ramatuelle
programme.desc: In 1988, Dee Dee Bridgewater was one of the first great jazz singers to perform at the Jazz Festival in Ramatuelle. In 2016, the story seems to repeat itself as her daughter China Moses took the stage at Ramatuelle. Over the years, China Moses has become a mature performer with a unique style: rocky voice, sharp sense of swing, and intense/energetic stage presence. After signing compilations dedicated to Dinah Washington and blues, Moses released in 2016 an album of his own compositions, entitled "Whatever". Get ready for a most entertaining performance combining jazz, soul, and hip-hop.

programme.title: Yumi Ito
programme.desc: An extraordinary collection of clips in all jazz genres from the most beautiful concerts and the most special festivals, performed by the finest jazz musicians.

programme.title: Charles Mingus, Jaki Byard, Dannie Richmond & Johnny Coles
programme.sub-title: Charles Mingus And Eric Dolphy live in Liège
programme.desc: Charles Mingus showcases an exceptional concert performed in April 1965 featuring his most celebrated lineup: Jaki Byard (piano), Dannie Richmond (drums), Johnny Coles (trumpet), Clifford Jordan (tenor sax) and the great Eric Dolphy (alto sax, flute and bass clarinet). Recorded within an eight-day span, less than three months before Dolphy's death, the three concerts showcase Mingus's visionary leadership and the band's incredible depth and diversity with unique performances and arrangements of classics including ‘So Long Eric' and the groundbreaking ‘Meditations On Integration'.

programme.title: Miles Davis
programme.desc: American trumpeter Miles Davis (1926-1991) was a pioneering jazz musician from the late 1940s to the late 1980s. His influence on 20th century music is hard to overstate, as he trailblazed bebop, cool jazz, hardbop, modal jazz, and electronic music. On October 11, 1964, Miles Davis performed at Teatro Dell'Arte in Milan. With tenor saxophonist Wayne Shorter, pianist Herbie Hancock, bassist Ron Carter and drummer Tony Williams, Davis performed Autumn Leaves, My Funny Valentine, All Blues, All of You, and Joshua.

programme.title: Stochelo Rosenberg & Peter Beets
programme.desc: The treasured compositions of guitarist Django Reinhardt, the founding father of hot club jazz, are engraved in everyone's memory. Although Reinhardt missed two fingers of his left hand, his virtuoso technique was unrivalled. Dutch guitarist Stochelo Rosenberg and pianist Peter Beets now have the pleasure to bring Django's music back to life with their infectious improvisations.

programme.title: Wes Montgomery
programme.sub-title: Herbie Man & Sonny Sharrock - Memphis underground
programme.desc: This selection of unforgettable performances by some of the most iconic and influential jazz guitarists in history showcases these legends' unique essence. Revel in Wes Montgomery's virtuosity as he performs the captivating “Nica's Dream” in Holland in 1965, and delight in the expressive beauty of his rendition of “Here's That Rainy Day”, recorded in London in that same year. Experience the timeless appeal of Joe Pass's “You Stepped Out of a Dream” and “You Turned The Tables on Me”, recorded live in Hanover in 1975. The interplay between Jim Hall and Atilla Zoller borders on the impossible as they perform “Extensions” in Hanover in 1973. Enjoy Jim Hall's lyrical solo performance of “I'm Getting Sentimental Over You” from 1964. Witness Sonny Sharrock's avant-garde fusion of jazz and rock in an exhilarating performance of “Peanut", recorded live in France in 1970. Sharrock is joined by flutist Herbie Mann in a soulful performance of “Memphis Underground” from 1969. Immerse yourself in the magic of jazz guitar!

programme.title: Omar Sosa, Childo Tomas, Ernesto Simpson & Leandro Saint-Hill
programme.desc: While always keeping one foot firmly anchored in the traditions of his home country, Cuba, Omar Sosa tirelessly explores music from the Caribbean to India, and West Africa to the Arab world. Since he left Cuba in 1993, the pianist has been blending his Afro-Cuban roots with jazz, hip hop, electro and world music. For his 2018 performance at Théâtre de Villefranche-sur-Saône, he brings to stage his Quarteto Afrocubano members Childo Tomas (electric bass & vocals), Ernesto Simpson (drums), and Leandro Saint-Hill (saxophones, flute, percussion & vocals). Together, they create a riveting instrumental dialogue. Celebrating rhythm in all its forms, this Omar Sosa concert is an intense and mystical experience.

programme.title: B.B.King
programme.sub-title: B.B. King Orchestra - The North Sea Jazz
programme.desc: The North Sea Jazz Festival is the largest indoor music festival in the world, known globally as the event where the past, present and future of jazz are featured within three days. Next to a firm base of jazz as the festival's staple music genre, many others, such as blues, soul, funk, or hip hop, pass by. Back in 1979, legendary American blues guitarist B.B. King gave an unforgettable performance for the audience in The Hague. Born in 1925 in a small town in Mississippi, 'Lucille' (as he nicknamed his guitar) helped him escape a miserable existence picking cotton. He arrived in Memphis in the late 1940s, where his cousin Bukka White taught him the tricks of the blues. Soon he developed his own style. King's virtuoso, narrative solos with lots of vibrato, have been an inspiration for most (rock) guitarists after him.

programme.title: Diana Ross & The Supremes
programme.desc: Diana Ross & Supremes- America's most successful female vocal group of all time was formed by four Detroit schoolgirls in the late 50s. Diana Ross (26 March 1944, Detroit, Michigan, USA), Betty McGlown (b. 1943, Detroit, Michigan, USA), Florence Ballard (b. 30 June 1943, Rosetta, Mississippi, USA, d. 22 February 1976, Detroit, Michigan, USA) and Mary Wilson (b. 6 March 1944, Greenville, Mississippi, USA) named themselves the Primettes in tribute to the local male group, the Primes - who themselves found fame in the 60s as the Temptations.

programme.title: Lenny Kravitz
programme.desc: American singer, songwriter, multi-instrumentalist, record producer, actor and arranger, whose "retro" style incorporates elements of rock, blues, soul, R&B, funk, jazz, reggae, hard rock, psychedelic, pop, folk and ballads. In addition to singing lead and backing vocals, Kravitz often plays all the guitar, bass, drums, keyboards, and percussion himself when recording. He won the Grammy Award for Best Male Rock Vocal Performance four years in a row from 1999 to 2002, breaking the record for most wins in that category as well as setting the record for most consecutive wins in one category by a male.

programme.title: David Grimal & Les Dissonances
programme.sub-title: Beethoven - Symphony No. 4 in B-flat major, Op. 60
programme.desc: Les Dissonances is a collective of artists founded by violinist David Grimal in 2004. The conductorless ensemble consists of musicians from the most prestigious European orchestras, international soloists, and young talents. In this performance, Les Dissonances perform Ludwig van Beethoven's Symphony No. 4 in B-flat major, Op. 60. Count Franz von Oppersdorff, who adored Beethoven's Symphony No. 2, offered the composer a large sum to write a similar work. Completed in the autumn of 1806, the symphony's first performance was at a private concert in Vienna in March of 1807. Symphony No. 4 is often overshadowed by its revolutionary predecessor and successor. With its lightweight and cheerful nature, Symphony No. 4 contrasts with the two aforementioned works. This performance was recorded at Opéra de Dijon, France, in 2013.

programme.title: David Grimal & Les Dissonances
programme.desc: Les Dissonances is a collective of artists founded by violinist David Grimal in 2004. The conductorless ensemble consists of musicians from the most prestigious European orchestras, international soloists, and young talents. In this performance, Les Dissonances perform Johannes Brahms' String Sextet No. 1 in B-flat major, Op. 18. The work is scored for two violins, two violas, and two cellos. Brahms wrote his only two string sextets at the very beginning of his career. String Sextet No. 1 was written in 1860. Brahms was one of the first to compose for this ensemble, blazing a trail for Antonín Dvořák, Pyotr Ilyich Tchaikovsky, Arnold Schoenberg, and others. This performance was recorded at Opéra de Dijon, France, in 2013.

programme.title: Claudio Abbado, Simón Bolívar Youth Orchestra & Anna Prohaska
programme.desc: Claudio Abbado conducts the Símon Bolívar Youth Orchestra at the Lucerne Easter Festival of 2010. Soloist is the young and talented Austrian soprano Anna Prohaska. On the program are Sergei Prokofiev's “Scythian Suite”, Op. 20, Alban Berg's Lulu Suite for soprano and orchestra, and Pamina's Aria from W. A. Mozart's opera The Magic Flute. The orchestra concludes with a performance of Pyotr Ilyich Tchaikovsky's Symphony No. 6, Op. 74.

programme.title: Gabriela Montero, Youth Orchestra of the Americas & Carlos Miguel Prieto
programme.desc: Venezuelan pianist Gabriela Montero is accompanied by the Youth Orchestra of the Americas conducted by Carlos Miguel Prieto. On the program are Maurice Ravel's Piano Concerto in G Major, as well as two of Montero's own works: the “Latin Concerto” and Improvisations. The performance took place in one of the world's most beautiful concert halls, the Teatro del Lago in Frutillar, located in the middle of the Patagonian plains. The concert hall, which opened its doors in 2010, stands on the banks of Chile's second-largest lake overlooking a volcano that is capped with snow the entire year. In an accompanying interview, Montero speaks about composing, improvising, and performing works of her own alongside those of others. She discusses her home country of Venezuela, where she no longer performs for political reasons.
